I"5<h3 id="about-devaid">About devAid</h3>

<p>A free mobile-friendly Bootstrap theme designed to help developers
promote their personal projects</p>

<h3 id="setup--usage">Setup &amp; usage</h3>

<p>devAid may be installed by simply downloading the .tar.bz2 folder from
the <a href="https://github.com/kevit/devaid-jekyll-theme/archive.tar.bz2">repository on
Github</a>.</p>

<p>After extracting the content from the folder into the selected
directory, you can type <code>jekyll serve</code> from the terminal, than open
your browser to <code>0.0.0.0:4000/</code> and you will find there.</p>

<p>Additionally it is possible to fork the repository and using Github
Pages as hosting. By following this way it will enough change the
<code>baseurl</code> value into the <code>_config.yml</code> file, with the directory
name of your project (for example /blog) or with a simply “/” (slash)
if you want install Emerald in the root.</p>

